icate addresses in the input list are consolidated into a single stop with combined delivery items, not visited twice.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior crosses preprocessing/state-handoff boundary: dedup+merge output must be consumed correctly by route construction so the stop is visited once. A pure unit test of merge logic can miss duplication reintroduced downstream. System is not required (no real OS/network dependency in behavior text). No LLM or multi-agent steps. Higher levels rejected due absence of infra/model requirements.","test_description":"Run the service pipeline with duplicated addresses carrying different delivery items; assert one consolidated stop exists with merged items and the produced route contains that stop exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.34,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
